Program: Outlook
Title: Kofi Annan Interview
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00ypf18
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 9 Oct 2012
In an extended edition of Outlook Kofi Annan - the former Secretary General of the United Nations - reflects on his 50 years in international diplomacy. Kofi Annan's memoir, written with Nader Mousavizadeh, is called: 'Interventions. A Life in War and Peace'.